OL,3,CYounger workers in England face 'place-
OL,4,Cbased' pay penalty, study warns
OL,6,FWorkers in the early stages of their
OL,7,Fcareer face a pay penalty for doing
OL,8,Fthe same job in a different part of
OL,9,FEngland, according to new analysis
OL,10,Fwhich unveils "stark and persistent"
OL,11,Fregional wage inequalities.
OL,13,FAn average employee in London earns
OL,14,Fnearly twice as much as the equivalent
OL,15,Fin Liskeard, in Cornwall, research by
OL,16,Fthe Resolution Foundation showed.
OL,18,FThe analysis suggests that higher
OL,19,Fwages are not driven by the people
OL,20,Fthat work there, but by the place in
OL,21,Fwhich they work.
