OL,3,CYounger workers in England face 'place-
OL,4,Cbased' pay penalty, study warns
OL,6,FBut the study suggests that a bigger
OL,7,Fjobs market does not necessarily equal
OL,8,Fhigher wages ` with, for example,
OL,9,Faverage workers in Cambridge earning
OL,10,F23% more than in the similarly-sized
OL,11,FLeicester.
OL,13,FInstead, a major driver of place-based
OL,14,Fpenalties come from where individual
OL,15,Ffirms choose to locate, meaning that
OL,16,Fif higher-paying firms relocated to a
OL,17,Fnew area then it could boost pay for
OL,18,Fthe local population, it found.
