OL,3,CYounger workers in England face 'place-
OL,4,Cbased' pay penalty, study warns
OL,6,F"It's often assumed that people are
OL,7,Fdriving these divides but, in fact,
OL,8,Fplace-based pay penalties are rife
OL,9,Facross England.
OL,11,F"A typical early career worker could
OL,12,Flose out on #1,300 a year just because
OL,13,Fof where their job is located.
OL,15,F"Policymakers at local, regional and
OL,16,Fnational levels can address these
OL,17,Fdivides by creating the conditions for
OL,18,Fhigh-paying firms to locate to their
OL,19,Fareas, while avoiding an arms race
OL,20,Fbetween regions in subsidies for firms.
